context: According to the 2010 Census, whites made up <a0_0><b5_0>51%<b5_0/><a0_0/> of Houston's population; 26% of the total population were non-Hispanic whites. Blacks or African Americans made up <a1_0><b6_0>25%<b6_0/><a1_0/> of Houston's population. American Indians made up 0.7% of the population. <a2_0><b7_0>Asians<b7_0/><a2_0/> made up 6% (1.7% Vietnamese, 1.3% Chinese, 1.3% Indian, 0.9% Pakistani, 0.4% Filipino, 0.3% Korean, 0.1% Japanese), while Pacific Islanders made up 0.1%. Individuals from some other race made up 15.2% of the city's population, of which 0.2% were non-Hispanic. Individuals from two or more races made up 3.3% of the city. At the 2000 Census, there were <a3_0><b8_0>1,953,631<b8_0/><a3_0/> people and the population density was 3,371.7 people per square mile (1,301.8/km²).
